Key Match Events: Australia won the ICC Men's ODI Cricket World Cup title for the sixth time after beating India by six wickets.
Travis Head made 137 in just 120 balls.
Australia restricted India to 240 on a slow surface and chased the target with 42 balls to spare.
Post-Match Reflections: Heartbreak for Rohit Sharma's team and millions of fans who were hopeful that the team would lift the World Cup for the third time in their history.
